{
  "texts": [
    "The calling can be done independently where each sample produces a single VCF file accompanied by a binary file that serializes every single candidate SV that has even a (CARD) 27) and is currently peaking in the M42 endeavor to sequence multiple hundreds of thousands of genomes.",
    "This also requires more efficient software to not just detect SVs but also to merge and produce a fully genotyped variant call format (VCF) file 28, 29.",
    "The improved degrees of error and lower cost for long reads are also starting to promote applications in medical or clinical space 30, 31.",
    "This is needed as several genes or regions of the genome remain a 'dark matter' 20, 32.",
    "Most of these genes (∼70%) can be assessed using long-read technologies, but several challenges remain 32."
  ]
}